74
00:03:21,828 --> 00:03:23,994
releases convection currents

75
00:03:23,994 --> 00:03:27,491
which causes the tectonic plates to move slowly.

76
00:03:27,491 --> 00:03:29,462
These are the 16 main tectonic plates

77
00:03:29,462 --> 00:03:32,604
that move slowly year after year.

78
00:03:32,604 --> 00:03:34,626
When they collide with each other,

79
00:03:34,626 --> 00:03:36,437
earthquakes happen.

80
00:03:36,437 --> 00:03:38,720
So, the countries and the areas

81
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:41,263
that lie on the boundaries of the tectonic plates

82
00:03:41,263 --> 00:03:44,162
are prone to earthquakes the most.

83
00:03:44,162 --> 00:03:46,196
And the thing about Japan is that

84
00:03:46,196 --> 00:03:48,121
it is situated at a place where

85
00:03:48,121 --> 00:03:51,642
four tectonic plates come together.

86
00:03:51,642 --> 00:03:53,892
The Pacific plate, the Philippine plate,

87
00:03:53,892 --> 00:03:56,789
the Eurasian plate, and 
the North American plate.

88
00:03:56,789 --> 00:03:58,483
This is the biggest reason why

89
00:03:58,483 --> 00:04:00,920
so many earthquakes are seen in Japan.

90
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:03,501
Among them, the Pacific plate stands out a bit.

91
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:07,991
Since it has the highest amount of tectonic activity.

92
00:04:07,991 --> 00:04:10,024
So, the boundary of the Pacific plate

93
00:04:10,024 --> 00:04:12,867
is known as the Pacific Ring of Fire.

94
00:04:12,867 --> 00:04:16,890
Because this causes the highest 
number of earthquakes in the world.

95
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:20,438
As well as the highest number of volcanoes. 

96
00:04:20,438 --> 00:04:23,382
To some extent, this is true for the other plates as well.

97
00:04:23,382 --> 00:04:25,325
And the countries located on their boundaries

98
00:04:25,325 --> 00:04:28,274
witness a higher frequency of earthquakes.

99
00:04:28,274 --> 00:04:31,248
For example, if you see India's northern boundary,

100
00:04:31,248 --> 00:04:33,835
the boundary between the Indian and Eurasian plates,

101
00:04:33,835 --> 00:04:36,362
that passes through Nepal,

102
00:04:36,362 --> 00:04:38,049
amidst the Himalayan mountains,

103
00:04:38,049 --> 00:04:40,948
this causes devastating earthquakes in Nepal.

104
00:04:40,948 --> 00:04:42,831
The earthquakes in North India,

105
00:04:42,831 --> 00:04:45,178
in Delhi and its surrounding regions,

106
00:04:45,178 --> 00:04:47,600
in most cases, their epicentre

107
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:50,792
lies between these two plates.

108
00:04:50,792 --> 00:04:53,941
Compare this with regions like 
Australia, Russia or Europe,

109
00:04:53,941 --> 00:04:56,788
where you rarely see any earthquakes.

110
00:04:56,788 --> 00:04:58,603
When was the last time you heard about

111
00:04:58,603 --> 00:05:00,367
a terrible earthquake in Australia?

112
00:05:00,367 --> 00:05:02,739
It's not like there have been 
no earthquakes in Australia at all.

113
00:05:02,739 --> 00:05:06,487
But the regions that lie in 
the middle of the tectonic plates,

114
00:05:06,487 --> 00:05:08,865
get earthquakes at a lower frequency.

115
00:05:08,865 --> 00:05:10,698
And when earthquakes do occur,

116
00:05:10,698 --> 00:05:12,211
they are not as devastating.

117
00:05:12,691 --> 00:05:14,019
And the reason behind this is that

118
00:05:14,019 --> 00:05:17,645
these major tectonic plates are 
made up of minor tectonic plates.

119
00:05:17,851 --> 00:05:21,246
And, at times, the collision 
between the major tectonic plates

120
00:05:21,246 --> 00:05:24,121
can be felt even in the middle of the plate.

121
00:05:24,532 --> 00:05:26,004
But depending on the way 
that these main tectonic plates

122
00:05:26,004 --> 00:05:28,746
collide with each other,

123
00:05:28,746 --> 00:05:31,020
various types of boundaries can be formed.

124
00:05:31,020 --> 00:05:33,290
Such as the Convergent boundary,

125
00:05:33,290 --> 00:05:36,171
when one plate collides and slips under the other.

126
00:05:36,171 --> 00:05:37,493
Or Divergent boundary,

127
00:05:37,493 --> 00:05:39,802
where both plates move away from each other.

128
00:05:39,802 --> 00:05:41,414
Or Transform boundary,

129
00:05:41,414 --> 00:05:45,106
when both plates move parallel against each other.

130
00:05:45,106 --> 00:05:47,621
Among these, the most dangerous earthquakes

131
00:05:47,621 --> 00:05:49,706
occur when convergent or 
transform boundaries are formed.

132
00:05:49,706 --> 00:05:52,313
And the boundary of the Pacific plate

133
00:05:52,313 --> 00:05:53,950
is a convergent boundary.

134
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:55,658
It has a specific sub-type

135
00:05:55,658 --> 00:05:57,278
known as the Subduction Zone.

136
00:05:57,278 --> 00:05:58,483
In the Subduction Zone,

137
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:00,555
causes the most powerful earthquakes

138
00:06:00,555 --> 00:06:02,671
because in this type of collision,

139
00:06:02,671 --> 00:06:04,595
when one plate collides with another,

140
00:06:04,595 --> 00:06:06,478
it goes right under the other

141
00:06:06,478 --> 00:06:08,001
submerging into the mantle.

142
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:09,668
And when this happens,

143
00:06:09,668 --> 00:06:10,717
as you can see in the diagram,

144
00:06:10,717 --> 00:06:12,954
a deep cavity or hole is formed under the sea

145
00:06:12,954 --> 00:06:14,669
on the boundaries of the two plates,

146
00:06:14,669 --> 00:06:16,480
which is called a Trench.

147
00:06:16,823 --> 00:06:20,000
These underwater trenches are 
often the deepest point in the ocean.

148
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:24,583
