to stop the force of tsunamis.

263
00:10:58,003 --> 00:10:59,555
They have built coastal dikes,

264
00:10:59,555 --> 00:11:01,068
which look like this.

265
00:11:01,068 --> 00:11:03,751
These are long structures built of stones.

266
00:11:03,751 --> 00:11:05,966
These dikes are very expensive to build,

267
00:11:05,966 --> 00:11:09,357
but they can successfully reduce the impact of tsunamis.

268
00:11:09,357 --> 00:11:12,730
Apart from these, tsunami evacuation towers are built.

269
00:11:12,730 --> 00:11:16,386
In areas with a high-risk of tsunami 
and a significant population,

270
00:11:16,386 --> 00:11:18,759
since people do not get a lot of time for evacuation,

271
00:11:18,759 --> 00:11:20,433
they are told to take shelter in these towers,

272
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:21,653
located at a high point,

273
00:11:21,653 --> 00:11:23,618
to be protected from the tsunamis.

274
00:11:23,618 --> 00:11:26,048
They have improved their warning systems.

275
00:11:26,048 --> 00:11:27,969
Evacuation drills are regularly conducted,

276
00:11:27,969 --> 00:11:30,616
to help the locals understand

277
00:11:30,616 --> 00:11:32,790
what they need to do in case of a tsunami.

278
00:11:32,790 --> 00:11:35,774
And how to prepare for rescue operations.

279
00:11:35,774 --> 00:11:38,900
And finally, they have built walls near the sea.

280
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:40,347
Sea walls.

281
00:11:40,347 --> 00:11:43,347
Japan has a 22,000-mile-long coastline

282
00:11:43,347 --> 00:11:48,087
40% of which is surrounded 
by these concrete sea walls.

283
00:11:48,087 --> 00:11:51,355
But, unfortunately, these walls 
are not always effective.

284
